on 10/20/03 07:47, librarian related:

 
> Let the bus idle for 20 minutes then replace the lifter if it still has
> not pumped up.

i think it is better to drive the bus, like on the highway, get the revs up
a bit, accelerate, decelerate, etc, rather than idling. you need to put load
on the lifters and build oil pressure, idling doesn't do that.

